.TH "MONGOC_MATCHER_NEW" "3" "2014-08-08" "MongoDB C Driver"
.SH NAME
mongoc_matcher_new()
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
mongoc_matcher_t *
mongoc_matcher_new (const bson_t *query,
                    bson_error_t *error);
.fi
.fi

Create a new
.BR mongoc_matcher_t
using the query specification provided.

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B query
A bson_t.
.LP
.TP
.B error
An optional location for a
.BR bson_error_t
or
.B NULL
\&.
.LP

.SH "ERRORS"

Errors are propagated via the
.B error
parameter.

.SH "RETURNS"

A newly allocated
.BR mongoc_matcher_t
that should be freed with
.BR mongoc_matcher_destroy(3)
when no longer in use. Upon failure,
.B NULL
is returned and
.B error
is set. This could happen if
.B query
contains an invalid query specification.


